.css","hash":"2afb6e7e24abf81c8b7b7d472fb0bb9b9a1eac16","modified":1482786691526}],"Category":[{"name":"Architecture","_id":"cix6kwsro0001siziky448f4d"}],"Data":[],"Page":[{"date":"2016-12-25T22:19:09.000Z","_content":"My name is Joe.\nEmail: fangzhou.external at gmail\nFeel free to contact me of any questions or feedbacks","source":"about/index.md","raw":"---\ndate: 2016-12-25 14:19:09\n---\nMy name is Joe.\nEmail: fangzhou.external at gmail\nFeel free to contact me of any questions or feedbacks","updated":"2016-12-25T23:05:31.000Z","path":"about/index.html","title":"","comments":1,"layout":"page","_id":"cix6kwtc10005sizix0v4i0js","content":"<p>My name is Joe.<br>Email: fangzhou.external at gmail<br>Feel free to contact me of any questions or feedbacks</p>\n","excerpt":"","more":"<p>My name is Joe.<br>Email: fangzhou.external at gmail<br>Feel free to contact me of any questions or feedbacks</p>\n"}],"Post":[{"title":"From monolithic to SOA - Uber's practice","date":"2016-12-25T05:05:13.000Z","description":"Why and how Uber change its architecture from monolithic mode to SOA","_content":"### Why\nAs core domain models grew and new features were introduced, our components became tightly coupled, and enforcing encapsulation made separation of concerns difficult. Continuous integration turned into a liability because deploying the codebase meant deploying everything at once.\n\n### New Challenges\n  - Obviousness\nToo many services would bring complexities on how to find and use them.\n  - Distributed API Safety\nDealing with unexpected argument, schema, calling...\n  - Resilience\nHow to deal with fault tolerance and latency?\n\n### Solution\n- **Thrift**\nThrift use strict contract binding to resolve 'Safety' concern.\n\n- **Hystrix** \nHystrix is a latency and fault tolerance library designed to isolate points of access to remote systems, services and 3rd party libraries, stop cascading failure and enable resilience in complex distributed systems where failure is inevitable.\nhttp://hot66hot.iteye.com/blog/2155036\nhttps://segmentfault.com/a/1190000005988895\n\n- **Finagle**\nFinagle is an extensible RPC system for the JVM, used to construct high-concurrency servers. Finagle implements uniform client and server APIs for several protocols, and is designed for high performance and concurrency.\nCore value: type Service[Req, Rep] = Req => Future[Rep]\n\n### Reference\n[Uber's article](https://eng.uber.com/soa/)\n[Hystrix](https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix)\n[Finagle](https://twitter.github.io/finagle/)","source":"_posts/From-monolithic-to-SOA-Uber-s-practice.md","raw":"---\ntitle: From monolithic to SOA - Uber's practice\ndate: 2016-12-24 21:05:13\ndescription: Why and how Uber change its architecture from monolithic mode to SOA\ntags: SOA, Architecture, Uber\ncategory: Architecture\n---\n### Why\nAs core domain models grew and new features were introduced, our components became tightly coupled, and enforcing encapsulation made separation of concerns difficult. Continuous integration turned into a liability because deploying the codebase meant deploying everything at once.\n\n### New Challenges\n  - Obviousness\nToo many services would bring complexities on how to find and use them.\n  - Distributed API Safety\nDealing with unexpected argument, schema, calling...\n  - Resilience\nHow to deal with fault tolerance and latency?\n\n### Solution\n- **Thrift**\nThrift use strict contract binding to resolve 'Safety' concern.\n\n- **Hystrix** \nHystrix is a latency and fault tolerance library designed to isolate points of access to remote systems, services and 3rd party libraries, stop cascading failure and enable resilience in complex distributed systems where failure is inevitable.\nhttp://hot66hot.iteye.com/blog/2155036\nhttps://segmentfault.com/a/1190000005988895\n\n- **Finagle**\nFinagle is an extensible RPC system for the JVM, used to construct high-concurrency servers. Finagle implements uniform client and server APIs for several protocols, and is designed for high performance and concurrency.\nCore value: type Service[Req, Rep] = Req => Future[Rep]\n\n### Reference\n[Uber's article](https://eng.uber.com/soa/)\n[Hystrix](https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix)\n[Finagle](https://twitter.github.io/finagle/)","slug":"From-monolithic-to-SOA-Uber-s-practice","published":1,"updated":"2016-12-25T23:05:31.000Z","comments":1,"layout":"post","photos":[],"link":"","_id":"cix6kwsrj0000sizivpb0uz6l","content":"<h3 id=\"Why\"><a href=\"#Why\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Why\"></a>Why</h3><p>As core domain models grew and new features were introduced, our components became tightly coupled, and enforcing encapsulation made separation of concerns difficult. Continuous integration turned into a liability because deploying the codebase meant deploying everything at once.</p>\n<h3 id=\"New-Challenges\"><a href=\"#New-Challenges\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"New Challenges\"></a>New Challenges</h3><ul>\n<li>Obviousness<br>Too many services would bring complexities on how to find and use them.</li>\n<li>Distributed API Safety<br>Dealing with unexpected argument, schema, calling…</li>\n<li>Resilience<br>How to deal with fault tolerance and latency?</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"Solution\"><a href=\"#Solution\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Solution\"></a>Solution</h3><ul>\n<li><p><strong>Thrift</strong><br>Thrift use strict contract binding to resolve ‘Safety’ concern.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Hystrix</strong><br>Hystrix is a latency and fault tolerance library designed to isolate points of access to remote systems, services and 3rd party libraries, stop cascading failure and enable resilience in complex distributed systems where failure is inevitable.<br><a href=\"http://hot66hot.iteye.com/blog/2155036\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external\">http://hot66hot.iteye.com/blog/2155036</a><br><a href=\"https://segmentfault.com/a/1190000005988895\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external\">https://segmentfault.com/a/1190000005988895</a></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Finagle</strong><br>Finagle is an extensible RPC system for the JVM, used to construct high-concurrency servers. Finagle implements uniform client and server APIs for several protocols, and is designed for high performance and concurrency.<br>Core value: type Service[Req, Rep] = Req =&gt; Future[Rep]</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"Reference\"><a href=\"#Reference\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Reference\"></a>Reference</h3><p><a href=\"https://eng.uber.com/soa/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external\">Uber’s article</a><br><a href=\"https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external\">Hystrix</a><br><a href=\"https://twitter.github.io/finagle/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external\">Finagle</a></p>\n","excerpt":"","more":"<h3 id=\"Why\"><a href=\"#Why\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Why\"></a>Why</h3><p>As core domain models grew and new features were introduced, our components became tightly coupled, and enforcing encapsulation made separation of concerns difficult. Continuous integration turned into a liability because deploying the codebase meant deploying everything at once.</p>\n<h3 id=\"New-Challenges\"><a href=\"#New-Challenges\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"New Challenges\"></a>New Challenges</h3><ul>\n<li>Obviousness<br>Too many services would bring complexities on how to find and use them.</li>\n<li>Distributed API Safety<br>Dealing with unexpected argument, schema, calling…</li>\n<li>Resilience<br>How to deal with fault tolerance and latency?</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"Solution\"><a href=\"#Solution\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Solution\"></a>Solution</h3><ul>\n<li><p><strong>Thrift</strong><br>Thrift use strict contract binding to resolve ‘Safety’ concern.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Hystrix</strong><br>Hystrix is a latency and fault tolerance library designed to isolate points of access to remote systems, services and 3rd party libraries, stop cascading failure and enable resilience in complex distributed systems where failure is inevitable.<br><a href=\"http://hot66hot.iteye.com/blog/2155036\">http://hot66hot.iteye.com/blog/2155036</a><br><a href=\"https://segmentfault.com/a/1190000005988895\">https://segmentfault.com/a/1190000005988895</a></p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Finagle</strong><br>Finagle is an extensible RPC system for the JVM, used to construct high-concurrency servers. Finagle implements uniform client and server APIs for several protocols, and is designed for high performance and concurrency.<br>Core value: type Service[Req, Rep] = Req =&gt; Future[Rep]</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"Reference\"><a href=\"#Reference\" class=\"headerlink\" title=\"Reference\"></a>Reference</h3><p><a href=\"https://eng.uber.com/soa/\">Uber’s article</a><br><a href=\"https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix\">Hystrix</a><br><a href=\"https://twitter.github.io/finagle/\">Finagle</a></p>\n"}],"PostAsset":[],"PostCategory":[{"post_id":"cix6kwsrj0000sizivpb0uz6l","category_id":"cix6kwsro0001siziky448f4d","_id":"cix6kwsrq0004sizifcxgaawm"}],"PostTag":[{"post_id":"cix6kwsrj0000sizivpb0uz6l","tag_id":"cix6kwsrp0002sizi4yddc2hn","_id":"cix6kwsrq0003sizilzjx5q3m"}],"Tag":[{"name":"SOA, Architecture, Uber","_id":"cix6kwsrp0002sizi4yddc2hn"}]}}